  <description><![CDATA[<p>One of <a data-udi="umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt’s</a> leading hotels, the unique Hotel Alex enjoys a superb central location and is beautifully furnished throughout, combining the modern and traditional for a luxurious ‘boutique’ feel. Family-run for over 50 years, the hotel receives consistently good feedback for its gourmet cuisine, excellent facilities and high level of service.</p>
<h2>Boutique hotel</h2>
<p>The Hotel Alex is a unique hotel set in the centre of Zermatt. Furnished to a high standard, this hotel ticks all the boxes for a memorable stay in <a data-udi="umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>. With a convenient location in <a data-udi="umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a>, you are close to the ski lifts, bars and restaurants - you can easily get on the mountain each day, or visit the attractions around resort and enjoy a drink or two at the end of the day. Throughout the hotel you can find alpine wood combined with stone to create a luxurious feel, and the public areas including the bar, restaurant and wellness area are all ideal spots to relax after a day of exploring Zermatt. </p>
<h2>Wellness and relaxation</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the slopes of Zermatt, take a moment to unwind in the wellness area. Have a dip in the pool, soothe your aches and pains in the sauna or steam-room, and have a rest in the solarium. For the ultimate treat, book a massage or treatment with the spa team. If you want to keep your fitness levels up, there is also a fitness room with a range of equipment and a sports court - have a game of badminton or tennis at the extensive indoor courts. </p>
<h2>Lounge and restaurant </h2>
<p>Each day you can enjoy a hearty buffet breakfast to fuel up for a day on the slopes. In the evening a three to five course set meal is served, using fresh and seasonal ingredients to create tasty dishes. The hotel is also home to the Alex Grill, serving meat and fish specialities from the Valais region - <span>the chefs use local and seasonal ingredients to conjure up new creations and innovative takes on the classics. Groups can enjoy the Bodega Bacchus, one of Zermatts most luxurious wine cellars serving Valais specialities and gourmet meals with global wine pairings. </span></p>
<p>There are some lovely areas in the hotel to socialise with friends and families including the Alex Bar,  enjoy a specially crafted cocktail or sit back and relax in the themed alcoves including the<span> ‘Highlander’ or the ‘Scottish Corner’. </span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
